{"id":14881866,"mediaExerciseId":"3851fe1d-1773-4682-8aa8-9905db69b202","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"24","chapterTitle":"Options and Corporate Finance","groupId":612498,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":822,"solutions":[{"id":6003665,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the impact on call option values, and on put, option values suppose the interest rate on T-bills suddenly and unexpectedly rises.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define some terms.\n\n- **Put Option** is a contract that gives a holder the right, but not the obligation to sell a stock.\n\n- **Call Option** is a contract that gives a holder the right to buy a stock.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Changes in interest rates directly affect option pricing. If the interest rate on T-bills suddenly and unexpectedly rises, then the value of the call option increases, and the value of the put option decreases. It is more valuable when interest rates are high and less valuable when interest rates are low relative to delay the payment.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/042f9baf25d7f7520173862c361cc6e6/94ee47ec65e3a2c01ffa18788a43e502/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/042f9baf25d7f7520173862c361cc6e6/94ee47ec65e3a2c01ffa18788a43e502/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"52415372-3b8b-42e7-a0c6-07258aa01d13","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratin